Production at Japan's mines and factories grew 6% in August from a year ago, and rose 2.9% from the previous month on an adjusted basis, the Ministry of International Trade and Industry said. 

The unadjusted mining and industrial production index stood at 112.0 (1980 equals 100).
The adjusted index was at 

Most categories, officials said, moved into the plus column when compared with the previous month. 

This compared with the situation in July when overall mining and industrial production fell an adjusted 2.1% from June, while rising 6.1% from a year ago. 

